-- Samsung Elec sees DRAM, NAND prices falling in Q1
-- 
-- Thu Jan 11, 2007 9:37pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/12/us-samsung-chip-price-idUSSEO26348420070112

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. ( 005930.KS ), the world's biggest maker of memory chips, expected a high-single digit percent decline in its dynamic random access memory (DRAM) price, with shipments rising 10 percent. 

 Cho Nam-yong, executive vice president for Samsung's semiconductor business, told a conference call on Friday the price of its NAND flash memory chips would likely fall less than 10 percent after recent sharp drops.